The disproportionality inherent in the composition of the [House of Parliament](/House_of_Commons_of_the_United_Kingdom) following the 1992 election was quantified at 13.59 according to the [Gallagher Index](/Gallagher_Index). This significant disparity primarily manifested between the [Liberal Democrats](/Liberal_Democrats_(UK)) and the [Conservatives](/Conservative_Party_(UK)), highlighting how the first-past-the-post system can distort the relationship between popular vote and parliamentary representation. A rather inconvenient truth for those who champion "fairness."

